post_text:
Today is National Suicide Awareness Day. The National Suicide Prevention Lifeline (@800273TALK) offers free, confidential crisis counseling 24/7/365 - and you don’t have to be in crisis to call. #SPM20 #NotAlone

September is National Suicide Prevention Awareness Month—a time to share resources and stories in an effort to shed light on this highly taboo and stigmatized topic. We use this month to reach out to those affected by suicide, raise awareness and connect individuals with suicidal ideation to treatment services. It is also important to ensure that individuals, friends and families have access to the resources they need to discuss suicide prevention. NAMI is here to help.
https://www.nami.org/get-involved/awareness-events/suicide-prevention-awareness-month

shared_text:
Minnesota Department of Human Services
May 28 at 2:03 PM ·

Starting today, Minnesota SNAP participants can purchase groceries online from Walmart and Amazon using their EBT cards. This is vital to maintain social distancing during the COVID-19 pandemic while helping Minnesotans put healthy food on their tables. More information is in a news release: http://mn.gov/dhs/media/news/index.jsp?id=1053-433606

For information about SNAP or applying for it, visit mn.gov/dhs/food-emergency or call the Minnesota Food helpline at 651-486-9860 or 888-711-1151.
#StaySafeMN

STA Families - thank you for your patience during this difficult time. Below is important information for next week:

Distance learning materials will be distributed at bus stops on Monday for scholars in PreK-5th grade. Scholars MUST be at their bus stop to get their work. Buses will leave STA at 10:00am and run the regular route. Please keep in mind the approximate time of arrival based on when your child(ren) get home from school when it was a regular school day.

Scholars who walk to school or get brought to and from school should come Monday from 10:00-2:00 to pick up their materials.

Middle School Scholars (6th-8th grade) should come Monday from 12:00-3:00pm to get their materials and Chromebook. Parents/Guardians MUST come with their child to receive a Chromebook and sign the user agreement.

If Monday does not work for you to pick up materials or Chromebooks(6th-8th grade only) please call the office at 612-588-3599 to make other arrangments.

post_text:
Distribución de Alimentos-
STA comenzará la distribución de alimentos el lunes 23 de marzo. Distribuiremos los alimentos a través de las paradas de autobús. Los autobuses saldrán de STA a las 10:00 am cada día. La comida consistirá en el desayuno y el almuerzo. Por favor, estén en la parada del autobús para recoger la comida.

Tengan en cuenta la hora aproximada a la que llegará el autobús. Por ejemplo, si su hijo llega a casa a las 2:50 en un día normal de escuela, el autobús probablemente estará llegando a la parada a las 10:20 para distribuir la comida.

Estamos pensando en todas nuestras familias durante este tiempo incierto. Continuaremos actualizando Facebook y el sitio web con información.
La distribución de alimentos en la escuela será de 8:00-9:00 para el desayuno y de 12:00-1:00 para el almuerzo. Cualquier niño menor de 18 años es elegible para el desayuno o el almuerzo.

Ms. Guy ❤️

post_text:
STA will begin food distribution on Monday, March 23rd. We will be distributing food via bus stops. Buses will leave STA at 10:00 am each day. The food will consist of breakfast and lunch. Please be at the bus stop to pick up the food.

Keep in mind the approximate time the bus will arrive. For example, if your child gets home at 2:50 on a regular school day the bus would likely be at the top at 1020 to distribute the food.

On-site food distribution will be from 8:00-9:00 for breakfast and 12:00-1:00 for lunch. If you come at 8:00am to pick up you can pick up breakfast and lunch. Any child under 18 is eligible for breakfast or lunch.

We are thinking about all our families during this uncertain time. We will continue to update Facebook and our website with information.

Be well - Ms. Guy

❤️

shared_text:
SAMARITANSFEET.ORG
The Perfect Pumas

Denise Duncan Blomberg is with Bridget Ruckdashel and 8 others.
January 29 at 4:44 PM ·

As part of my work with Samaritan's Feet International, I have been blessed to have had so many opportunities to serve some amazing people, alongside some amazing volunteers in some pretty amazing places, but this shoe distribution in North Minneapolis on April 10, 2019 was a day like no other. Not only was it the 1st anniversary of Ryan's death, but it was also a day full of love, hope, inspiration and joy, thanks to some amazing friends, donors, teachers and staff coming together to bless the lives of the 410 students who attend the Sojourner Truth Academy. I am always grateful to be able to share Ryan's story so that his life can continue to have significance in the lives of so many others.

To see the many ways you can get involved with Samaritan's Feet, please go to www.samaritansfeet.org or contact me at dblomberg@samaritansfeet.org.

#shoesofhope #RememberingRyan💜
